text: Conjurer may refer to: * Conjurer, someone who exercises evocation, the act of calling upon or summoning a spirit, demon, god or other supernatural agent, in the Western mystery tradition * Conjurer, a performer of magic ==Arts and entertainment== * The Conjurer (painting), a 1502 painting by Hieronymus Bosch * Conjurer (composition), a 2007 composition by John Corigliano * Conjurer (film), a 2008 American supernatural horror film ==See also== * Conjuration (disambiguation)
title: Conjurer
